{{Infobox figure skater |name= Scott Davis |image= |caption= |fullname= Scott Davis |altname= |country= [[United States of America|United States]] |formercountry= |birth_date= {{birth date and age|1972|1|29}} |birth_place= [[Great Falls, Montana]] |hometown= [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]] |residence= |height= 5'9" (175 cm) |partner= |formerpartner= |coach= |formercoach= |choreographer= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= [[Broadmoor SC]] |retired= }} '''Scott Davis''' (born January 29, 1972 in [[Great Falls, Montana]]) is an American [[figure skater]]. He is the 1993 & 1994 [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships|U.S. national champion]].<ref name=sdavis2>{{cite web|title=Major Leageue Figure Skating Championships|last=Hutchinson|first=Claudyne Cassella|publisher=Major League Figure Skating|url=http://www.mlfskating.com/shell.asp?Target=index|accessdate=August 24, 2011}}</ref> In 1994, he defeated 1988 Olympic gold medalist [[Brian Boitano]] to win the title. Davis represented the [[United States at the 1994 Winter Olympics]], where he placed 8th.
In the years following, Davis suffered from [[vertigo (medical)|vertigo]] and had problems with his jump consistency. Although he continued to compete until the 1998 season, after 1995 he never again qualified for a World or Olympic team. After turning professional, he appeared in an ice show production of the musical ''[[Grease (musical)|Grease]]''.
Known for his extraordinary spinning ability, Davis was coached by [[Kathy Casey]] in [[Colorado Springs]] and [[Galina Zmievskaya]] in [[Simsbury, Connecticut]]. He coaches in [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]], [[Canada]], where his students include [[Vaughn Chipeur]].
Davis is an ISU Technical Specialist.<ref>{{PDFlink|[http://www.isu.org/vsite/vfile/page/fileurl/0,11040,4844-179484-196702-110011-0-file,00.pdf ISU Communication No. 1409]|381&nbsp;KB}}</ref> He was a technical specialist for the men's event at the [[2006 World Figure Skating Championships]].<ref>[http://www.isufs.org/results/wc2006/ ISU World Figure Skating Championships<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
